<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="bend-v">bend <strong><em>v</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /bend/    美 /bend/  </p>
<p>(bent, bent)</p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1-vt-vi">1.★ <strong>vt &amp; vi (使) 弯曲：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>You have to bend your knees to sit down. 
你得屈膝才能坐下。</p><footer>外研④ – 3</footer></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>(使) 弯腰：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He <strong>bent down / over</strong> and picked up a book from the floor. 
他俯身从地上捡起一本书。</p></div>

<h4 id="3">3.★ <strong>(路) 转弯：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The road bends to the right after a few yards. 
这条路在几码远的地方转向右方。</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">固定搭配</h2>
<h3 id="bend-to-sbs-will">bend to sb’s will</h3>
<p>1.<strong>[正式用语] 屈服于某人的意愿</strong>  </p></div>